        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 18 at 4:32PM MDT until May 18 at 5:15PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM MDT/532 PM CDT/, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles
west of Russell Springs, or 25 miles northwest of Scott State Lake,
moving north at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Winona around 540 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Mingo.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 60 and 62.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT/900 PM CDT/ for
northwestern and west central Kansas.

A tornado watch remains in effect for the warned area. Tornadoes can
develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Although a tornado is not
immediately likely, if one is spotted act quickly and move to a place
of safety inside a sturdy structure, such as a basement or small
interior room.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
